#Gif Creator

This project is a Gif Creator application that allows you to create animated GIFs 
from a series of images or video files. It provides various features and effects like 
fade in/out, star wipe, and window blinds transitions.

##Installation

1) Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/your-username/gif-creator.git

2)Install the required dependencies:
pip install imageio moviepy

##Usage

1) Add your images or video files to the appropriate directories:

2) For images: Place your image files in the "Image-Slideshow" directory.
For videos: Place your video files in the "Gif-Creator" directory.
Modify the filenames in the Python code to match your image or video files:

3) For the slide show: Update the filenames list in the first code block of create_slideshow.py with the filenames of your images.
For the GIF conversion: Update the VideoFileClip argument in the second code block of create_gif.py with the filename of your video.
Run the Python scripts to create the GIF:

4) For the slide show: Execute create_slideshow.py.
For the GIF conversion: Execute create_gif.py.
Find the generated GIF in the project directory with the name "output.gif".

##Acknowledgements

This project makes use of the following libraries:

imageio (https://imageio.readthedocs.io/en/stable/)
moviepy (https://zulko.github.io/moviepy/)

##Optional Enhancements
You can explore additional enhancements for the Gif Creator project, such as:

Adding more transition effects or allowing users to choose different effects.
Providing options to adjust the duration of each frame or transition.
Implementing a user-friendly interface to select images or videos and customize the GIF creation process.
Feel free to contribute to the project by adding new features, fixing bugs, or suggesting improvements.



